## Priority Assignment

### Priority Scheme (ARM NVIC Example)

| Priority Level | Assignment | Preempts |
|----------------|-----------|----------|
| 0 (highest) | Safety-critical (watchdog, fault) | All |
| 1 | Hard real-time (motor control, ADC) | 2-15 |
| 2 | Communication (SPI, I2C, UART) | 3-15 |
| 3 | Timer ticks (RTOS systick) | 4-15 |
| 4-15 | Application interrupts | Lower only |

### Priority Assignment Rules

- [ ] Higher priority = more time-critical, not more important
- [ ] No two unrelated ISRs share the same priority (unless grouping is intentional)
- [ ] RTOS syscall-safe API boundary is documented (e.g., `configMAX_SYSCALL_INTERRUPT_PRIORITY` in FreeRTOS)
- [ ] ISRs above the RTOS threshold do NOT call any RTOS API
- [ ] Priority scheme is documented in a project-level table

