## Shared State Protection

### Critical Section Patterns

| Pattern | Scope | Duration Limit | Use Case |
|---------|-------|---------------|----------|
| Disable all IRQs | Global | < 5 us | Atomic multi-word update |
| Disable specific IRQ | Single peripheral | < 10 us | Peripheral state update |
| RTOS critical section | Tasks + ISRs below threshold | < 10 us | Shared data structure |
| Atomic operations | Single word | 0 (hardware) | Counters, flags |

### Protection Rules

- [ ] Every variable shared between ISR and task has documented protection
- [ ] `volatile` keyword used on all ISR-modified variables
- [ ] Critical sections are as short as possible (no computation inside)
- [ ] No nested critical sections (or nesting count is implemented)
- [ ] Atomic operations preferred over critical sections for simple flags

### Atomic Access Pattern

```c
/* Use compiler intrinsics for atomic operations */
__atomic_store_n(&shared_flag, 1, __ATOMIC_RELEASE);
uint32_t val = __atomic_load_n(&shared_counter, __ATOMIC_ACQUIRE);
__atomic_add_fetch(&event_count, 1, __ATOMIC_RELAXED);
```

