## ISR Testing

### Testing Approach

| Test Type | Method | Coverage |
|-----------|--------|----------|
| ISR timing | GPIO + oscilloscope | WCET verification |
| ISR stress | Trigger at max rate for 60s | Stability under load |
| Queue overflow | Fill queue, verify graceful handling | Error path |
| Priority inversion | Simulate contention scenario | Deadlock detection |
| Spurious IRQ | Trigger IRQ without valid source | Robustness |

### Testing Checklist

- [ ] Each ISR has measured WCET on target hardware
- [ ] ISR storm test passed (max rate for > 1 minute)
- [ ] Deferred work queue tested at capacity
- [ ] ISR disabled/enabled sequence tested (no missed interrupts)
- [ ] Nested interrupt scenario tested (if nesting is used)

---

## Common Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Risk | Fix |
|-------------|------|-----|
| `printf` in ISR | Blocks for ms, corrupts output | Log to buffer, print in task |
| `malloc` in ISR | Non-deterministic timing | Pre-allocate from pool |
| Long computation in ISR | Blocks all lower-priority IRQs | Defer to task |
| Disabling IRQs for > 100 us | Missed interrupts, jitter | Redesign shared data access |
| Reading multi-byte value without protection | Torn read | Atomic or critical section |
| Clearing IRQ flag after processing | Re-entry if slow | Clear flag first |
